Password Strength Checker Flask App

#This Flask-based web application validates the strength of user passwords according to custom rules:

-Password must be exactly 9 characters long
-Must contain at least 4 characters
-Must contain at least 2 letters
-Must contain at least 3 alphanumeric(special characters)

#The app provides clear success or error messages and can be extended with enhanced UX features such as WTForms or JavaScript validation.

##Features
- Built with Flask
- Styled using Bootstrap 5
-Immediate feedback on password validity after form submission
-Simple and clean user interface with HTML templates

##Technical stack
-Flask/python
-html
-css
-bootstrap
-javascript


##Installation and Setup
Prerequisites
-Python 3.7 or higher
-Flask web framework (pip install flask)

##Installation Steps
-Clone or download the repository.
-Navigate into the project directory.

##Optionally create a virtual environment:

-python -m venv <name_of_environment>
-source venv/bin/activate    or  Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

Install dependencies:
-pip install -r requirements.txt

##Run the Flask app:

flask run python <flask_name>.py

Open your browser to http://127.0.0.1:5000 and test the password validator.

##Usage
-Enter a password in the input field.
-Submit the form to see validation results.
-Password must meet all criteria for success.

##Project Structure

password-strength-checker-flask/
│
├── app.py                   # Main Flask app and password validation function
├── requirements.txt         # Project dependencies
├── templates/               # HTML templates
│    └── index.html          # Form and message display
├── static/                  # Optional folder for CSS/JS assets
└── README.md                # This documentation
